<paragraph id="C17E54FA6A516B88F41B549A2067CD38" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91C94DB134732EA39FCD47D1982B36EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In selecting a lectotype for 
<taxonomicName id="B1227593EDD641CDD773D9AB79565EE5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pedatus">
<emphasis id="3F772F8F590384BCB4B3919F46A3FBB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Convolvulus pedatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
we have chosen MA606866 in preference to MA603824 (cited by Nelson, 1997; 393) because it has 
<normalizedToken id="4C8BAC07FBC958E65ED5B3229C2CB4F6" originalValue="Sessé">Sesse</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="F5D1DC4D131A783FABE106B3FE8C5635" originalValue="Moçiño’s">Mocino's</normalizedToken>
original manuscript notes attached and these correspond to the protologue in Flora Mexicana.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
